From: Nicolin Chen <b42378@freescale.com>
Date: Mon, 5 Aug 2013 14:50:50 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 0034/1074] ENGR00273838-6 arm: dtsi: imx6qdl: Remove
 fifo-depth for ssi

Remove fifo-depth for ssi and let the driver use the default value 8.

Doing this modification is because 15 fifo-depth, an odd number, is
not working perfectly with ssi dual-fifo mode by setting sdma water
mark to 13 (result from 15 - 2).

Acked-by: Wang Shengjiu <b02247@freescale.com>
Signed-off-by: Nicolin Chen <b42378@freescale.com>
[Original patch taken from git://git.freescale.com/imx/linux-2.6-imx.git]
Signed-off-by: Biyao Zhai <biyao.zhai@windriver.com>
---
 arch/arm/boot/dts/imx6qdl.dtsi |    3 ---
 1 files changed, 0 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm/boot/dts/imx6qdl.dtsi b/arch/arm/boot/dts/imx6qdl.dtsi
index e199279..fcf445c 100644
--- a/arch/arm/boot/dts/imx6qdl.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm/boot/dts/imx6qdl.dtsi
@@ -241,7 +241,6 @@
 					dmas = <&sdma 37 1 0>,
 					       <&sdma 38 1 0>;
 					dma-names = "rx", "tx";
-					fsl,fifo-depth = <15>;
 					fsl,ssi-dma-events = <38 37>;
 					status = "disabled";
 				};
@@ -254,7 +253,6 @@
 					dmas = <&sdma 41 1 0>,
 					       <&sdma 42 1 0>;
 					dma-names = "rx", "tx";
-					fsl,fifo-depth = <15>;
 					fsl,ssi-dma-events = <42 41>;
 					status = "disabled";
 				};
@@ -267,7 +265,6 @@
 					dmas = <&sdma 45 1 0>,
 					       <&sdma 46 1 0>;
 					dma-names = "rx", "tx";
-					fsl,fifo-depth = <15>;
 					fsl,ssi-dma-events = <46 45>;
 					status = "disabled";
 				};
